headline: Elon Musk: Tesla owners can 'lend' self-driving EVs to robotaxi fleet
summary: Tesla (TSLA) released fourth quarter results after Wednesday's market close, reporting adjusted earnings of $0.50 per share compared to estimates of $0.45 and revenue of $24.90 billion versus estimates of $25.11 billion.In Wednesday's earnings call, Tesla CEO Elon Musk spoke more about his plans for the EV company's full self-driving (FSD) capabilities and robotaxi services, adding that Tesla owners will be able to "lend" their vehicles to the growing autonomous robotaxi service "kind of like how Airbnb works."The company seeks to expand its robotaxi business to other US cities as it currently operates in Austin, Texas, and San Francisco, California. content.title: Elon Musk: Tesla owners can 'lend' self-driving EVs to robotaxi fleet
content.description:
Tesla (TSLA) released fourth quarter results after Wednesday's market close, reporting adjusted earnings of $0.50 per share compared to estimates of $0.45 and revenue of $24.90 billion versus estimates of $25.11 billion.

In Wednesday's earnings call, Tesla CEO Elon Musk spoke more about his plans for the EV company's full self-driving (FSD) capabilities and robotaxi services, adding that Tesla owners will be able to "lend" their vehicles to the growing autonomous robotaxi service "kind of like how Airbnb works."

The company seeks to expand its robotaxi business to other US cities as it currently operates in Austin, Texas, and San Francisco, California. Musk announced last week that Tesla has removed its safety monitoring feature Autopilot, enabling the robotaxis to reportedly be fully autonomous.

Watch the video above to hear more.

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out Yahoo Finance.

headline: Robinhood to Vie for Key Retail Role in Mega SpaceX IPO
summary: Robinhood is jockeying with several Wall Street banks to secure a big slug of coveted SpaceX stock to sell directly to its retail investors, said the people, who asked to not be identified because the details aren’t public.  The company would likely offer the shares through its IPO Access platform, which lets users buy stock at the IPO price, before they trade on the open market.  Elon Musk’s rocket and satellite company is considering earmarking a significant portion of the shares for retail investors, the people said.

headline: Airbnb to Announce Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2025 Results
summary: Airbnb, Inc. (NASDAQ: ABNB) today announced that the company's fourth quarter and full year 2025 financial results will be released after market close on February 12, 2026. The company's shareholder letter will be made available on the Airbnb Investor Relations website at https://investors.airbnb.com.
